好评: As a Star Wars fan I pretty enjoy this game. It tells a lot of cool stories about the few years after order 66. As for the combat it might be really hard for those who haven't played this kind of game before, but once you get the hang of it it can be really fun, the sound effects and animations are really cool and rewarding. There's also a lot of things to explore and a lot of collectibles.
The only things I don't like about this game are puzzles and maps. I'm never a fan of puzzle solving and in this game the puzzles just seem kinda unnecessary to me, sure it adds more contents to the game but I just think there's too much of them and they're sometimes really confusing, you can ask for hints but they barely help, so it just drains my patience so much and it's really a buzz killer. And as for the map, it's usually not a problem in the early stage but as you explore the map just gets more and more complicated until you have no idea where is where, and there is no fast travel or GPS in the game either so it's really like going through a maze, that can also drain my patience so much
Generally it's not a bad game. If you are a Star Wars fan and love combat games then it's absolutely a great game for you. But if you are somewhat impatient about puzzles and stuff like me, you might wanna reconsider about it
